## Quality Checks

### Must Pass
- ✅ RMSE < 5 points (pricing errors small)
- ✅ Hazard rates always positive
- ✅ Q(t) monotonically decreasing
- ✅ No single bond with error > 10 points

### Nice to Have
- 🎯 RMSE < 2 points (good fit)
- 🎯 RMSE < 1 point (excellent fit)
- 🎯 Parity equation holds (for bullets): B(T)Q(T) + Ξ(T) + r_b Π(T) = 1

### Red Flags
- 🚩 RMSE > 10 points → Bad fit, investigate
- 🚩 Negative hazard rates → Invalid curve
- 🚩 Q(t) increasing → Optimization failed
- 🚩 All bonds have same-sign errors → Systematic bias

